===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|point|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|point|lang=fro||a point, dot, full stop, period, speck, hole, stitch, point of time, moment, difficulty, etc.}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|punctum||a point, puncture|lang=la}}, prop. a hole punched in, substantive use of {{term|punctus|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{term|pungō||I prick, punch|lang=la}}. Displaced native {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|ord||point|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|ord||point|lang=ang}}.

